org.numenta.nupic.network

Class PublisherSupplier

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.numenta.nupic.network.PublisherSupplier
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.util.function.Supplier<Publisher>, Persistable

    public class PublisherSupplier
extends java.lang.Object
implements Persistable, java.util.function.Supplier<Publisher>

    Ascribes to the Supplier interface to provide a Publisher upon request. This supplier is expressed as a lambda which acts as a "lazy factory" to create Publishers and set references on the Network when get() is called.

    The old way of creating Publishers has now changed when the PAPI is used. Instead, a PublisherSupplier is used, which ascribes to the Supplier interface which acts like a "lazy factory" and kicks off other needed settings when a new Publisher is created...

    The basic usage is: 

      Supplier supplier = PublisherSupplier.builder()
      .addHeader("dayOfWeek, timestamp")
      .addHeader("number, date")
      .addHeader("B, T")
      .build();
  
  // Since Suppliers are always added to Sensors we do...
  
  Sensor> sensor = Sensor.create(
      ObservableSensor::create, SensorParams.create(
          Keys::obs, new Object[] {"name", supplier})); // <-- supplier created above
          
  --- OR (all inline in "Fluent" fashion) ---
  
  Sensor> sensor = Sensor.create(
      ObservableSensor::create, SensorParams.create(Keys::obs, new Object[] {"name", 
          PublisherSupplier.builder()                                                // <-- supplier created fluently
              .addHeader("dayOfWeek, timestamp")
              .addHeader("number")
              .addHeader("B, T").build() }));

    • Method Detail

      • get

        public Publisher get()

        Implementation of the Supplier interface that returns a newly created Publisher.

        The Publisher.Builder is passed a Consumer in its constructor which basically triggers a call to Network.setPublisher(Publisher) with the newly created Publisher - which must be available so that users can get a reference to the new Publisher that is created when Network#load() is called.

        Specified by:
        get in interface java.util.function.Supplier<Publisher>
        Returns:
        a new Publisher
